The paper deals with graph theory and algorithms, specifically the problem of partitioning graphs into clusters with small diameter while removing a small fraction of edges. This falls under the categories of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Graph Theory (cs.GT), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
